30/01/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The government said Thursday (29 January) it plans to open a new border crossing to Kosovo.
The checkpoint, near the village of Dobrune of Hasi, is intended to improve control and prevent illegal crossings and human trafficking.
Currently there is only one border crossing to Kosovo, at Morine, near Kukes.
In other news, Albanian Finance Minister Arben Malaj thanked Britain Thursday for supporting developmental projects.
He met with Robin Milton of the UK Department for International Development, who called for more financial support from EU countries to accelerate Albania's reform process.
(ATA - 29/01/04)
